George Bush. § 4413. Executive Board(a) CompositionThe Board shall have an Executive Board composed of—(1) the chairman of the Board;(2) the vice chairman of the Board;(3) the secretary of the Board;(4) the treasurer of the Board; and(5) an at-large member of the Board elected by the Board at its initial meeting.(b) VacanciesIn the case of any vacancy which occurs in the position of at-large member before the expiration of such member’s term, the Board shall elect a replacement to complete that term.(c) MeetingsThe Executive Board shall hold not more than 4 regular meetings per calendar year. Special meetings may be held upon the call of the chairman or 3 members of the Executive Board.(d) QuorumA majority of the Executive Board shall constitute a quorum.(e) PowersThe Executive Board may hold and use all the powers of the Board, subject to the approval of the Board.(Pub. L. 99–498, title XV, § 1506Oct. 17, 1986100 Stat. 1603 § 4414. General powers of Board(a) In generalIn carrying out the provisions of t
